        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/littlemax28/{size}/7549_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-04-16T07:53:56.080Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi,</p>\n<p>The ‚Äúlink device‚Äù process is good. But when you need to unlink device the existing aprouch is not always workable and intuitive not mentioning data-security concerns.</p>\n<p>Existing aprouch: you need to unlink device from mobile app and in addition to that manually clear data from windows (for example) app.</p>\n<p>Preferred aprouch: when you unlink device from mobile app it brakes the syncronization of unlinked device and clear all data from that device. Additionally, in order to make the process intuitive add ‚ÄúUnlink device‚Äù to main command bar/toolbar which will perform existing ‚ÄúClear data‚Äù functionality.</p>\n<p>This is the way cloudbased messengers usually work and that is what you waiting from signal too. It has huge sense is some cases:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You don‚Äôt have any more access to unlinked device;</li>\n<li>Anyhow some device was linked without your approval and you want to stop data leaking.</li>\n</ol>",
