        "id": 59689,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Herohtar",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-04-16T16:58:24.134Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I‚Äôm not sure there is much use to this. If you still have access to the Desktop computer, just uninstall Signal ‚Äì that deletes the data.</p>\n<p>If you no longer have access to the device for some reason, unlinking will still prevent any new messages from being synced, so there is no additional risk there. If you‚Äôve properly secured the desktop then the data should be relatively safe.</p>\n<p>Also, the only way a ‚Äúclear data‚Äù feature would work is if that device still had internet access and could connect to the Signal servers. If someone were intentionally trying to get your Signal Desktop data, all they would have to do is disconnect it from the internet to prevent any ‚Äúclear data‚Äù messages.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"littlemax28\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"13263\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/littlemax28/48/7549_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> littlemax28:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Anyhow some device was linked without your approval and you want to stop data leaking.</li>\n</ol>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This scenario is not possible unless someone physically steals your mobile device, links it, and then gives it back, which is very unlikely.</p>\n<p>Also, if they were going to do that and were actually capable of pulling it off, they would probably do it with a modified client that didn‚Äôt respect any ‚Äúclear data‚Äù commands from the server, so such a feature wouldn‚Äôt be helpful there.</p>",
