      {
        "id": 62958,
        "name": "",
        "username": "sunu27",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-05-10T21:43:43.372Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I understand everything you said except for, ‚ÄúIf you‚Äôve properly secured the desktop then the data should be relatively safe.‚Äù  Security is an ongoing battle, and we do what‚Äôs considered reasonable given what‚Äôs available at the time - that‚Äôs why it‚Äôs important to keep your software updated.  If you lose your computer, then the software will become outdated and thus the longer time passes, the more vulnerable your data will be.  The mobile version allows an extra layer of security - I have to swipe my fingerprint whenever I open the app.  I‚Äôm sure it‚Äôs not foolproof (nothing is), but it‚Äôs a good, reasonable measure.  The fact that there‚Äôs a scenario where clear data would not work doesn‚Äôt mean this feature should not be considered.  Rather, it should be noted and prioritized based on the likelihood of a computer being connected to the internet.</p>",
