        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/ee7513/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-12-28T02:14:01.051Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A much needed functionality. I think Signal can design the desktop app or other apps in such a way - when the apps gets connected to the internet, it should first look for if it‚Äôs been unlinked, if yes then it should just start deleting everything without leading to the chat screen. I think the unlinked app alone should be capable of doing this.</p>\n<p>I‚Äôm not sure if it‚Äôs technically possible or not.</p>",
