        "cooked": "<p>Technically possible, probably yes, but it would require the desktop app to start on boot in the background, if you want this to happen when the computer boots, not just when opening the app. That would use up energy faster.</p>\n<p>My desktop also sometimes unlinks because of inactivity and I would not want it to delete all data when that happens. I don‚Äôt think that‚Äôs expected behaviour either.</p>",
