        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"mortal_engin3\" data-post=\"12\" data-topic=\"13263\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/ee7513/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> mortal_engin3:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Currently even after unlinking it just shows all the previous convos, makes no sense.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I think it does make sense. When my Desktop is unlinked and I don‚Äôt have my phone on me or don‚Äôt have an internet connection to re-link, I still want to be able to access previous conversations to look things up, even if I can‚Äôt recieve new messages.</p>",
